Package jinngine.collision

Interface Summary
BroadphaseCollisionDetection Broad-phase collision detection is the process of finding objects in a simulation, that are in close proximity of each other.
BroadphaseCollisionDetection.Handler A handler for broad-phase collision detection events.
 

Class Summary
ExhaustiveSearch A naive broad-phase collision detection algorithm.
GJK Implementation of the Gilbert-Johnsson-Keerthi algorithm, for computing the distance between convex objects and/or closest points.
RayCast Performs a collision query between a ray in space and a convex shape, defined by a support mapping.
SAP2 Better Sweep-and-prune implementation, replacing the old SweepAndPrune.java
SweepAndPrune Sweep and Prune implementation of the BroadphaseCollisionDetection interface.
